main event: A UFO sighting was reported in the Midwest and Southwest U.S. on July 25, 1961.
interesting points: The object was described as a high-speed, small white object leaving a trail as it moved up to an altitude above the horizon.
The observers could not confirm a definite sighting of an airborne object, suggesting the observation may have been a reflection or ballistics of a high-speed small object.
A bright new comet was discovered by an observer in Seattle, Washington on July 23, 1961, which had a well-defined nucleus, a tall covering about 23 degrees, and an antitail.
Several air and ground observers reported seeing a stationary object with a tail-like feature, though the ground observers could not see the tail.
The object was spotted by a civil jet aircraft and another aircraft, and remained stationary for about an hour before being obscured by clouds.
sighted object: A high-speed, small white object; a bright new comet; a stationary object with a tail-like feature
location: Midwest and Southwest U.S.; Seattle, Washington
witnesses: Pilots, aircraft crew, and ground observers
